under the supervision of Special Agent Peter Burke.

53
00:01:45,411 --> 00:01:46,201
是的  長官
Yes, ma'am.

54
00:01:46,561 --> 00:01:48,141
戴著追蹤腳環
While confined to a tracking anklet,

55
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:49,591
你協助博爾克探員
you've helped Agent Burke clear

56
00:01:49,591 --> 00:01:52,311
取得了94%定罪率的驚人成績
an impressive 94% conviction rate.

57
00:01:53,831 --> 00:01:55,091
我們合作很棒
We work well together.

58
00:01:55,881 --> 00:01:57,101
看起來是
It would seem so.

59
00:01:58,031 --> 00:01:59,601
最近逮捕的馬修·凱勒
The recent arrest of Matthew Keller,

60
00:01:59,601 --> 00:02:01,791
是聯調局十大通緝犯之一
one of the FBI's top 10 most wanted fugitives,

61
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:04,771
並追回了一批他偷竊的珍貴藏品
the recovery of a priceless collection of artwork he stole

62
00:02:04,771 --> 00:02:07,011
你真是改過自新的典型
You are the poster boy for reform.

63
00:02:07,381 --> 00:02:08,431
誰能想到呢
Who would have thought?

64
00:02:10,801 --> 00:02:12,921
你作為罪犯加入了司法系統
You came into this legal system as a criminal.

65
00:02:12,921 --> 00:02:15,891
聽證會成員要弄清的問題是  你是否已改過
The question before this board today is -- have you changed?

66
00:02:16,251 --> 00:02:17,311
我相信我改過了
I believe I have.

67
00:02:18,761 --> 00:02:19,801
在接下來兩天中
Over the next two days,

68
00:02:19,801 --> 00:02:22,141
我們將訪談一些和你親近的熟人
we'll be interviewing some of your closest acquaintances

69
00:02:22,151 --> 00:02:22,971
以及同事
and colleagues.

70
00:02:22,971 --> 00:02:25,411
然後我們會讓你回來進行最後陳述
Then we'll have you back to make a final statement,

71
00:02:25,461 --> 00:02:26,761
屆時博爾克探員
at which time Agent Burke

72
00:02:26,761 --> 00:02:28,781
將給出總結性建議
will give his summary recommendation.

73
00:02:29,001 --> 00:02:30,021
還有問題嗎
Any questions?

74
00:02:30,071 --> 00:02:30,881
沒有了  長官
No, ma'am.

75
00:02:31,441 --> 00:02:34,781
不過我想說過去兩年是我一生
But may I say that the last two years of my life

76
00:02:34,781 --> 00:02:35,521
最棒的...
have been the best --

77
00:02:35,521 --> 00:02:38,171
兩天會給你足夠的時間進行陳述
You'll have time for all that two days from now.

78
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:39,081
是的  長官
Yes, ma'am.

79
00:02:39,091 --> 00:02:40,741
令人讚歎啊  卡夫瑞先生
This is impressive, Mr. Caffrey.

80
00:02:41,241 --> 00:02:44,581
希望你本人和文件中所描述的相符合
I hope the real you lives up to who you are on paper.

81
00:02:44,901 --> 00:02:46,741
希望不辜負您的期望
I hope to exceed your expectation.

82
00:02:52,761 --> 00:02:53,841
你可以自由離開了
You're free to go.

83
00:02:58,931 --> 00:02:59,711
自由離開
"Free to go."

84
00:03:00,191 --> 00:03:02,121
真是個鼓舞人心的短語
Quite an inspiring turn of phrase.

85
00:03:02,271 --> 00:03:04,661
不過"自由留下"對我來說更合適
Except "You're free to stay" might be more appropriate.

86
00:03:05,111 --> 00:03:06,141
感覺如何
How's it looking?

87
00:03:06,141 --> 00:03:07,371
都有可能
Flip a coin.

88
00:03:08,931 --> 00:03:10,931
無論委員會如何判決
Regardless of what the committee decides,

89
00:03:11,241 --> 00:03:12,501
這裡就是我家了
this is my home now.

90
00:03:13,971 --> 00:03:15,501
而我會一直在你身邊
And I am right beside you.

91
00:03:17,111 --> 00:03:19,111
在同樣的紐約開始嶄新的生活
Make a brand-new start of it in old New York.

92
00:03:22,391 --> 00:03:24,491
當你重新開始時
Well, when you make that brand-new start,

93
00:03:24,581 --> 00:03:25,651
我有驚喜給你
I've got a surprise.

94
00:03:25,651 --> 00:03:27,551
-什麼驚喜  -大驚喜
- What kind of surprise?  - A huge one.

95
00:03:27,911 --> 00:03:30,341
能讓大犬星座都黯然失色
Makes Canis Majoris look like a night light.

96
00:03:30,581 --> 00:03:32,381
不過我不會再多說
But I will say no more.

97
00:03:32,821 --> 00:03:33,981
我也不問了
I'll ask no more.

98
00:03:36,571 --> 00:03:37,541
看起來你的證人列表裡
There seems to be someone missing

99
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:40,271
少了一個人
from your commutation witness list.

100
00:03:40,331 --> 00:03:41,261
抱歉
Yeah, sorry about that,

101
00:03:41,261 --> 00:03:42,941
不過讓一位著名罪犯為我說話
but having a known felon speak for me

102
00:03:42,941 --> 00:03:45,321
